      "span_text": "Fourth, we cannot say that we have estimated the 'definitive' measure of the elasticity of hours with respect to wages: Hanel et al. have highlighted the importance of explicitly accounting for the entry and exit decisions of nurses when modeling nurses labor supply decisions, where these entry and exit decisions might be said to reflect judgments about the 'whole of the advantages and disadvantages' of these different employments."
